# Kconfig entry for Murata SCH16T IMU driver.
# Add this block to drivers/iio/imu/Kconfig (in-tree), or use
# it stand-alone for an out-of-tree build.

config SCH16T
    tristate "Murata SCH16T IMU driver"
    depends on SPI
    select IIO_BUFFER
    select IIO_TRIGGERED_BUFFER
    help
      Say Y or M here to enable support for the Murata SCH16T series
      6-DOF inertial measurement units (gyroscope + accelerometer)
      connected over SPI.

      Supported variants:
        - SCH16T-K01  (high-sensitivity gyro, 1600–6400 LSB/dps)
        - SCH16T-K10  (standard-range gyro,   100–400  LSB/dps)

      The driver registers with the IIO subsystem and exposes angular
      velocity (rad/s), linear acceleration (m/s²) and temperature
      channels through sysfs and the IIO triggered-buffer interface.

      To compile this driver as a module, choose M here. The module
      will be called sch16t.
